🧾 Trading Journal API — Endpoint Documentation

Base URL:

/api/v1

All protected routes require:

Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
🔐 AUTH
POST /auth/register

Create new user.

Body
{
  "email": "user@email.com",
  "password": "string"
}
Response
{
  "message": "User created successfully"
}
POST /auth/login
Body
{
  "email": "user@email.com",
  "password": "string"
}
Response
{
  "access_token": "jwt",
  "refresh_token": "jwt",
  "token_type": "bearer"
}
POST /auth/refresh
Body
{
  "refresh_token": "jwt"
}
Response
{
  "access_token": "new_jwt",
  "token_type": "bearer"
}
👤 USER
GET /users/me

Returns current authenticated user.

🏦 ACCOUNTS
POST /accounts

Create trading account.

Body
{
  "name": "FTMO Account",
  "initial_balance": 10000,
  "currency": "USD"
}
GET /accounts

List all user accounts.

GET /accounts/{account_id}

Get single account details.

DELETE /accounts/{account_id}

Soft delete account.

📊 STRATEGIES
POST /strategies

Create strategy.

Body
{
  "name": "London Breakout",
  "description": "Breakout during London open"
}

Rules:

Admin can create global strategies

Users can create personal strategies

GET /strategies

List strategies (global + user-created)

📈 TRADES
POST /trades

Create new trade.

Body
{
  "account_id": 1,
  "symbol": "EURUSD",
  "entry_price": 1.0850,
  "stop_loss": 1.0830,
  "take_profit": 1.0900,
  "risk_amount": 100,
  "max_duration": 120,
  "timeframe": "M5",
  "session": "London",
  "strategy_id": 3,
  "image_url": "https://..."
}
Behavior

Status = ongoing (default)

RR calculated automatically

Risk validated

Trade linked to user

PATCH /trades/{trade_id}

Update trade dynamically.

Allowed updates:

exit_price

status

image_url

notes

If:

status = closed

System automatically:

Calculates PnL

Determines win/loss

Updates account balance

Updates drawdown

Stores outcome_status

GET /trades

Query params:

?account_id=
?status=
?symbol=
?strategy_id=
?from_date=
?to_date=
?page=
?page_size=
GET /trades/{trade_id}

Return single trade.

DELETE /trades/{trade_id}

Soft delete.

